FBIS4-49870 "drchi092_a_94004" FBIS-CHI-94-092 Daily Report 12 May 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Hong Kong Foreign Ministry Holds Weekly News Conference Foreign Ministry Holds Weekly News Conference Criticizes Remark on DPRK Aid OW1205095394 Beijing XINHUA in English 0934 GMT 12 May 94 OW1205095394 Beijing XINHUA English BFN [Text] Beijing, May 12 (XINHUA) -- The remark made by the U.S. Assistant Secretary Winston Lord at the Senate Subcommittee of Foreign Relations is totally groundless, said a Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman here today. At a weekly press conference here this afternoon, Spokesman Wu Jianmin made the statement when asked to comment on a report that on May 4, Lord indicated at the Senate Subcommittee of Foreign Relations that China in the past possibly aided the Democratic People's Republic of Korea's ballistic missile program, and surely helped its nuclear program. Wu said "such a remark is totally groundless and entirely irresponsible".
